The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 The second part of the budget session of the Assembly will begin on June 27. The session, in which departmental budgets will be passed, is likely to continue till the first week of August. Parliamentary affairs minister Probodh Sinha said some important bills, relating to education and power, will also be tabled. An appropriation bill is to be tabled by July 31.

 Justice Jayanta Biswas of the high court passed an order on Tuesday asking the state election commissioner to ensure that polling officers for the June 19 civic elections follow the notification of the central election commission issued on June 4, 2000.

 he notification requires polling officers to check the identity cards of voters. The high court order followed a petition by Israil Khan, who is contesting from ward 45.

 Sale of liquor has been prohibited from June 17 to 21 because of the Calcutta Municipal Corporation elections. The state government announced the ban on Tuesday.

 A 58-year-old man died after falling into a well in Patrapara, under Jagachha police station in Howrah, early on Tuesday. Police said Sunil Jana, a resident of Surkimill in Patrapara, fell into the well of his rented house around 6 am. The body was recovered by the fire brigade. An unnatural death case has been registered.

 Gajraj Singh, 55, died after being run over by a taxi in Salt Lake around 5 pm on Tuesday. Singh was crossing a road near AE block when the taxi knocked him down. He was taken to a local hospital, where doctors pronounced him dead. The taxi driver fled. 

 One man died and another was injured early on Tuesday after being hit by a Calcutta Municipal Corporation lorry in Maniktala. While Ram Chandra Yadav, 55, died on the spot, Brajeshwar Rabidas was admitted to NRS Medical College and Hospital with critical injuries.

 A 50-year-old pedestrian died and another was seriously injured after they were hit by a tram on Rabindra Sarani early on Tuesday. Both were rushed to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital, where one of them died. 

 The Academy of Clinical Medicine and Allied Science, in collaboration with the Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, will release a book on clinical immunology on June 18. A seminar on Future of Medicine and Healthcare will be held during the day. Swami Prabhananda, secretary of the institute, will attend the programme. 

 A 15-year-old NCC cadet, Rajesh Bajoria, was seriously injured after being hit by a vehicle at the crossing of Kidderpore Road and Lovers Lane on Tuesday morning. Police said he was taken to SSKM Hospital and later shifted to a nursing home.

 Traffic on College Street was disrupted for nearly half-an-hour on Tuesday afternoon as a group of students set up a blockade to protest ?police excesses? on Jadavpur University students. The blockade was lifted after senior police officers came to the spot.

 Bhalo-Basha, a de-addiction and rehabilitation centre for drug addicts and alcoholics, will organise awareness programmes from June 23 to 25.

 TO HSBC for organising a programme with children to spread awareness about the environment




